      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/22/2/13/14",
      "text": [
        ": إن علياً قال: كان لي أن أقتل المولي وأجهز على الجريح ولكني تركت ذلك للعاقبة من أصحابي؛ إن جرحوا لم يقتلوا، والقائم له أن يقتل المولي ويجهز على الجريح."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.abdullah-al-shahin": [
          "(15) Ali bin al-Husayn narrated from Muhammad bin Ali al-Kufi from Abdurrahman bin Abu Hashim from Abu Khadeeja from Abu Abdullah as-Sadiq (as) that Amirul Mo’mineen (as) had said: “I could have killed the fleers and finished off the wounded (warriors) but I did not do fearing for the end of my companions that if they might be wounded, they would not be killed. But al-Qa’im (as) is permitted to kill the fleers and to finish off the wounded.”"
        ]
      }
    },
